RESEARCH_MUNICIPALITY.notes: Seattle operates under a mayor-council form of government. The Mayor and two of the nine City Council members are elected at-large, while the remaining seven Council members are elected by district. Bruce Harrell is the current Mayor. As of November 2025, there is an ongoing mayoral election between Bruce Harrell and Katie Wilson, but Bruce Harrell is the current mayor. Mark Solomon and Debora Juarez were appointed to their respective council positions to fill vacancies in January 2025 and July 2025, respectively, and will serve until a successor is elected. The City Attorney (Ann Davison) and Municipal Court Judges (Faye Chess, Andrea Chin, Anita Crawford-Willis, Willie Gregory, Catherine McDowall, Damon Shadid, Pooja Vaddadi) are also elected officials.
